{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nPass-4 coaching (move registry + deterministically rendered notes + guide_url deep-links into docs/plan-review-criteria-guide.md) currently runs only over SURVIVING ADVISORY findings. Blocking findings - the ones an agent MUST remediate before claim - get no coaching note and no guide_url. Field data: the E6/F1 oracle-strictness finding family recurred 3-5 consecutive rounds on tickets fde0/0ee8/76d2 because agents reworded ACs instead of adding the demanded executable oracle; a guide link plus a move-shaped nudge on the block itself is the cheapest one-round-remediation lever. The reviewer/writer separation must be preserved exactly as-is: moves come from the locked registry, prose is rendered deterministically, the C1 subject validator still rejects code/imperatives/solutions.\n\n## What\nCoaching over blocking findings must be widened at BOTH execution seams, plus the prompt and renderer:\n- Bespoke (non-workflow) path: widen the Pass-4 coach invocation in src/rebar/llm/plan_review/passes.py from advisory-only to advisory+blocking, tagging each coaching entry with the source finding's decision (\"block\" | \"advisory\").\n- Workflow path (the v3 engine, authoritative in production): in src/rebar/llm/workflow/gates/plan-review.yaml, widen the coach_inputs binding (currently `surviving: ${{ steps.decide.outputs.surfaced }}`) to the union of blocking + surfaced advisory findings, and update the coach_gate branch `when:` condition so the coach step fires when EITHER blocking or advisory findings survive. In src/rebar/llm/workflow/workflow_ops.py, widen `plan_review_coach_inputs` (reads ctx.inputs \"surfaced\") and `plan_review_coach` (reads ctx.inputs \"surviving\") to carry the widened set.\n- Prompt + listing header: src/rebar/llm/reviewers/plan_review_coach.md currently frames the task as \"SURVIVING advisory findings\" and src/rebar/llm/review_kernel/coach.py hardcodes the listing header `## Surviving advisory findings (by id)`. Reword both to decision-neutral \"surviving findings\" (parameterize the header label), so the prompt never contradicts its input.\n- guide_url: attach to blocking findings' coaching notes exactly as for advisories today (src/rebar/llm/plan_review/orchestrator.py:515-530 passthrough-additive field).\n- CLI: `rebar review-plan` renders the coaching line + guide link for blocking findings the same way it does for advisories (src/rebar/_cli/_llm_commands.py, the existing `-> <coaching> [<link>]` renderer).\n- Sidecar: coaching entries for blocking findings flow through the existing coaching[] persistence unchanged (additive; the decision tag is a new optional field on coaching entries, not a schema break).\n\n## Scope\nIN: pass-4 finding-set widening on both seams (passes.py + plan-review.yaml/workflow_ops.py), decision tag, prompt/header rewording, guide_url attach, CLI rendering, unit tests. OUT: any change to the move registry contents, the subject validator, blocking/advisory decisions, thresholds, or the sidecar schema beyond the optional decision tag. OUT: conflict-detection between findings (parked epic grumpy-gland-rose).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] A plan review whose verdict contains blocking findings emits a coaching entry (move_id + rendered note + guide_url) for each blocking finding. Oracle: new unit test asserting a synthetic verdict with 1 block + 1 advisory yields 2 coaching entries, where the block's entry carries decision=\"block\" and guide_url and the advisory's carries decision=\"advisory\" and guide_url; `python -m pytest tests/unit -k \"coach\" -x` green.\n- [ ] The workflow path produces the same widening: a workflow-executed plan review over a verdict with blocking findings passes the union to the coach op. Oracle: unit test over `plan_review_coach_inputs`/`plan_review_coach` (tests/unit/workflow/) asserting blocking findings appear in the coach inputs and outputs.\n- [ ] The coach prompt and listing header no longer say \"advisory\": Oracle: `grep -ni \"advisory\" src/rebar/llm/reviewers/plan_review_coach.md` returns no hits framing the input set as advisory-only, and the rendered listing header for a mixed set reads decision-neutral (unit test asserts the header text).\n- [ ] Blocking-finding coaching notes pass the same C1 subject validation as advisory notes. Oracle: existing subject-validator tests extended to a blocking-finding case; suite green.\n- [ ] `rebar review-plan` output for a BLOCK verdict shows the coaching line + guide link under each blocking finding. Oracle: CLI rendering unit test asserting the rendered text contains the guide_url for a blocking finding.\n- [ ] `make lint && make typecheck && make test` all pass."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784093145040521001,"uuid":"73fd3da6-27a8-488c-ac21-2c6407720bff"}